    {
      "sender": "Heymian",
      "user_id": "UADQ9V8PK",
      "message": "@dlluncor (or anyone else) - an objections to me lifting the requirement that only site admins can run refiner scripts in their own repos?",
      "time": "09:33",
      "timestamp": "1560875592.228200",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "dlluncor",
      "user_id": "U3UA06MFD",
      "message": "For security reasons, I would be opposed to it",
      "time": "09:35",
      "timestamp": "1560875700.229900",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "dlluncor",
      "user_id": "U3UA06MFD",
      "message": "Why do we want to lift that restriction?",
      "time": "09:35",
      "timestamp": "1560875711.230300",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "Heymian",
      "user_id": "UADQ9V8PK",
      "message": "well it’s kind of annoying to have to setup things in an org owned repo to grant script execute permission",
      "time": "09:37",
      "timestamp": "1560875823.231600",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "Heymian",
      "user_id": "UADQ9V8PK",
      "message": "what’s the security reason?",
      "time": "09:37",
      "timestamp": "1560875856.232200",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "Ashish",
      "user_id": "U3UJ09DJ6",
      "message": "Let's not do it until we have assessed this carefully.",
      "time": "09:40",
      "timestamp": "1560876029.232800",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "Ashish",
      "user_id": "U3UJ09DJ6",
      "message": "This impacts infrastructure.",
      "time": "09:40",
      "timestamp": "1560876041.233400",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "Ashish",
      "user_id": "U3UJ09DJ6",
      "message": "One person's poorly written UDF can impact infrastructure resources.",
      "time": "09:41",
      "timestamp": "1560876079.234500",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "Ashish",
      "user_id": "U3UJ09DJ6",
      "message": "Sometimes I wonder whether we should allow UDF execution per person on a case by case basis until we have figured out a way to sandbox UDFs.",
      "time": "09:42",
      "timestamp": "1560876148.236400",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "sudeep",
      "user_id": "UCWRN72EP",
      "message": "Or another suggestion can we decouple admin and execute permission. So that we can give temporary execute grants.\n\nAt SC training a number of them want to play around with UDF's but we need to do ACL setup to make it happen. And that can again cause infra issues anyway.",
      "time": "09:42",
      "timestamp": "1560876168.237000",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "sudeep",
      "user_id": "UCWRN72EP",
      "message": "this can be a temporary stop gap until we sandbox UDFs",
      "time": "09:43",
      "timestamp": "1560876189.237500",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "sudeep",
      "user_id": "UCWRN72EP",
      "message": "and the permission grant can be set to auto expire in 6 hours (or something reasonable)",
      "time": "09:43",
      "timestamp": "1560876219.238500",
      "is_reply": false
    }
